<article>
    <h1>Brass Lion goes greener for its gins</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200809/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-09"><time>2020-08-09</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | FOOD &amp; DRINK</span>
        - <span role="byline">An&#xAD;jali Ragu&#xAD;ra&#xAD;man</span>
    </section>

    <p>Brass Lion Dis­tillery, Sin­ga­pore’s first full-fledged mi­cro dis­tillery, is now the pro­ducer of pos­si­bly the most sus­tain­able spirit avail­able here, with all as­pects – from sourc­ing and dis­till­ing its gins to prod­uct dis­tri­bu­tion– be­ing han­dled lo­cally.</p>
    <p>The dis­tri­bu­tion of its core range – Sin­ga­pore Dry Gin, But­ter­fly Pea Gin and Pahit Pink Gin – has been helmed by pre­mium spir­its dis­trib­u­tor Proof & Com­pany since last month.</p>
    <p>And from this month, Brass Lion’s flag­ship Sin­ga­pore Dry Gin is also part of Proof & Co’s EcoSpir­its plat­form, which sup­plies spir­its for ho­tels, restau­rants and bars.</p>
    <p>A world’s first, EcoSpir­its’ patent-pend­ing closed-loop dis­tri­bu­tion sys­tem dra­mat­i­cally re­duces the use of glass bot­tles by us­ing 4.5-litre re­us­able ves­sels called EcoTotes.</p>
    <p>They are sent out to bars, which can use them to re­fill ex­ist­ing bot­tles in the bar up to 40 times, af­ter which they are sent back to the dis­tillery to be sani­tised and re­filled.</p>
    <p>Us­ing EcoTotes will also make the Sin­ga­pore Dry Gin about 25 per cent more af­ford­able for es­tab­lish­ments that have been pur­chas­ing them in glass bot­tles.</p>
    <p>Ms Jamie Koh, founder and chief ex­ec­u­tive of Brass Lion Dis­tillery, says: “In ad­di­tion to dis­till­ing lo­cally and sourc­ing our botan­i­cals within a 5km ra­dius of the dis­tillery, we will now be able to sig­nif­i­cantly re­duce our glass and pack­ag­ing waste.</p>
    <p>“This low­ers our car­bon foot­print and al­lows us to pass on the cost sav­ings to our venue part­ners. We are proud to be able to do our small part for the environmen­t.”</p>


</article>

